Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @butternut squash{1} then halve lengthways and scoop out the seeds. Chop it widthways into 2cm slices, then chop into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop the butternut squash on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil, sprinkle over the @chermoula spice mix{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden on the outside and soft in the middle, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil in large #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the red onion, cook until soft and golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

While the onion cooks, halve the @lemon{1} and squeeze half the juice into a #small bowl{}. Add the @tahini{2%tbsp}, @honey{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @water{}, stir together with a #fork{} until well combined. Taste and add more lemon juice, salt or pepper to taste. Add a splash more water if it's a bit thick.

Once the onion is soft, stir in the @balsamic vinegar{1%tbsp}, cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @water{}, @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp} and @?lemon juice{}, stir, bring to the boil and simmer until reduced slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add in the lentils, bring to the boil, remove the pan from the heat. Set aside.

Meanwhile, roughly tear the @serrano ham{3%rashers} apart into pieces. Break up the @feta cheese{100%g} into small chunks. Re-heat the lentil mixture if necessary and once the squash is cooked, add it to the pan with the lentils, add half the feta and stir to combine.

Spoon the lentil and squash mixture into #bowls{} and top with the @pea shoots{40%g} and remaining feta. Drizzle with the dressing and share the ham between the bowls. Enjoy!

> Tender roasted butternut squash with salty serrano ham and the tart taste of feta is a delicious combination made in foodie heaven. Finish with a drizzle of honey-tahini dressing for a fresh, autumnal-tasting salad.